 tcw to reestablish itself as a standalone firm the arrangement was described as amicable for tcw and crescent the working relationship of the two companies remains close the two share management fees for existing clients following the separation the firm was renamed crescent capital group referencesedit  company briefstcw group inc new york times november    attanasio makes mark on city team in short time the business journal of milwaukee april    societe generale banks on tcw to build its reach in alternatives pensions  investments april   french bank takes a stake in trust company new york times april   tcwcrescent mezzanine and canterbury mezzanine capital join forces july    wwwmoneymanagementlettercompdfmmlpdf money management letter july   tcw agrees to split off crescent capital group external linksedit crescent capital group company website tcwcrescent mezzanine the funded of up to  million investment in tcwcrescent mezzanine partners iv los angeles city employees retirement system  notification of up to  million investment in tcwcrescent mezzanine partners v los angeles city employees retirement system  v t e private equity and venture capital investment firms investment strategy venture growth mezzanine secondaries leveraged buyout history history of private equity and venture capital early history of private equity private equity in the s private equity in the s private equity in the s investors angel investor commercial bank corporate venture capital crowdfunding family office endowment fund of funds highnetworth individual institutional investor insurance company investment bank merchant bank pension fund sovereign wealth fund private equity firms venture capital firms portfolio companies retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlecrescentcapitalgroupoldid categories private equity firms of the united statesdrexel burnham lambertmezzanine capital investment firmsamerican companies established in hidden categories pages using deprecated image synta